    "Similarly, humans can be still eaten by disabled predators (Corbett, 1944).",
    "In books dedicated chiefly to this problem (Jordania, 2014 (Jordania,, 2017)), I argued that humans demonstrate all the characteristics of aposematic features in every possible modality: audio, visual, olfactory, and behavioral (not only in body odor, as pointed out by Leakey in 1967 and Weldon in 2018).",
    "The following several sections discuss the most important human aposematic characteristics.",
